OL,3,CCancer deaths 50% higher in Wales'
OL,4,Cdeprived areas
OL,6,FCancer death rates are almost 50%
OL,7,Fhigher for people living in the most
OL,8,Fdeprived areas of Wales, compared to
OL,9,Fthose living elsewhere.
OL,11,FA new report from Cancer Research UK
OL,12,Ffound that there are around 1,400
OL,13,Fadditional cancer deaths in Wales each
OL,14,Fyear which are linked to socioeconomic
OL,15,Finequality.
OL,17,FAround a tenth of cancer diagnoses in
OL,18,FWales are connected to deprivation
OL,19,Fwith many of these deaths being caused
OL,20,Fby factors such as smoking.
